questions.question: If the points with position vectors $P(\lambda \hat{i} - 2\hat{j} + 3\hat{k})$, $Q(\hat{i} + \mu\hat{j} + 7\hat{k})$, and $R(3\hat{i} + 11\hat{j} + 11\hat{k})$ are collinear, then the value of $(\lambda^2 + 2\mu)$ is:

The measured value of $L$ is $20.0 \text{ cm}$ known to $1 \text{ mm}$ accuracy and the time for $100$ oscillations of the pendulum is found to be $90 \text{ s}$ using a wrist watch of $1 \text{ s}$ resolution. The percentage error in the determination of $g$ is approximately:

system is given an angular speed $\omega $ about the

circle in gravity free space. Then the stretch in
the spring is :

A particle of mass $m$ is moving in a straight line with momentum $p$. Starting at time $t = 0$, a force $F = kt$ acts in the same direction on the moving particle during time interval $T$ so that its momentum changes from $p$ to $3p$. Here $k$ is a constant. The value of $T$ is:

A circular hole of radius $\frac{R}{4}$ is made in a thin uniform disc having mass $M$ and radius $R$, as shown in the figure. The moment of inertia of the remaining portion of the disc about an axis passing through the point $O$ and perpendicular to the plane of the disc is:

Match List I with List II regarding the orbital parameters of a planet:

$$\begin{array}{ll} \pmb{\text{List I}} & \pmb{\text{List II}} \\ A. \text{ Kinetic energy} & I. \text{ } -\frac{GMm}{a} \\ B. \text{ Potential energy} & II. \text{ } \frac{GMm}{2a} \\ C. \text{ Total energy} & III. \text{ } \frac{Gm}{r} \\ D. \text{ Escape energy (per unit mass)} & IV. \text{ } -\frac{GMm}{2a} \end{array}$$

(Where $a =$ orbital radius, $r =$ planet radius, $M =$ Sun mass, $m =$ planet mass)

A calorimeter of water equivalent $20 \text{ g}$ contains $180 \text{ g}$ of water at $25^\circ\text{C}$. $m$ grams of steam at $100^\circ\text{C}$ is passed through the water until the final temperature of the mixture becomes $45^\circ\text{C}$. The value of $m$ is __________.

(Take latent heat of vaporization of water $L_v = 540 \text{ cal/g}$ and specific heat of water $s_w = 1 \text{ cal/g}^\circ\text{C}$)
For a particular ideal gas which of the following graphs represents the variation of mean squared velocity of the gas molecules with temperature?

Assume there are two identical simple pendulum clocks. Clock - 1 is placed on the earth and Clock - 2 is placed on a space station located at a height h above the earth surface. Clock - 1 and Clock - 2 operate at time periods 4 s and 6 s respectively. Then the value of h is -
(consider radius of earth $R_{E}=6400 \mathrm{~km}$ and $\mathrm{g}$ on earth $10 \mathrm{~m} / \mathrm{s}^{2}$ )

The source is moving with a speed of 19.4 m s^{$$-$$1} at an angle of 60^{o} with the source observer line as shown in the figure. The observer is at rest. The apparent frequency observed by the observer (velocity of sound in air 330 m s^{$$-$$1}), is

A point charge of $-5.0 \text{ nC}$ is located at the center of a spherical Gaussian surface of radius $10 \text{ cm}$. The electric flux passing through the surface is __________ $\text{N m}^2 \text{C}^{-1}$.

(Given $\epsilon_0 = 8.85 \times 10^{-12} \text{ C}^2 \text{ N}^{-1} \text{ m}^{-2}$)
The equivalent capacitance of the system shown in the following circuit is:

Two identical electric kettles are connected first in series and then in parallel across the same mains voltage. The ratio of the time taken to boil the same quantity of water in the series connection to that in the parallel connection is:

A uniform magnetic field is restricted within a region of rafius r. The magnetic field changes with time at a rate ${{d\overrightarrow B } \over {dt}}$. Loop 1 of radius R > r encloses the region r and loop 2 of radius R is outside the region of magnetic field as shown in the figure. Then the e.m.f. generated is

questions.question: An electromagnetic wave is propagating along the X-axis. At a certain point and time, the magnitude of its electric vector is $|E| = 12 \text{ V/m}$. The magnitude of its magnetic vector $|B|$ at that same point and time is:
Which figure shows the correct variation of applied potential difference ($V$) with photoelectric current ($i$) at two different intensities of light ($I_1 < I_2$) of same wavelengths:

Given below are two statements
Statement I : The law of radioactive decay states that the number of nuclei undergoing the decay per unit time is inversely proportional to the total number of nuclei in the sample.
Statement II : The half of a radionuclide is the sum of the life time of all nuclei, divided by the initial concentration of the nuclei at time t = 0.
In the light of the above statements, choose the most appropriate answer from the options given below :
questions.option_a: Statement I is incorrect but statement II is correct
questions.option_b: Both statement I and statement II are correct
questions.option_c: Both statement I and statement II are incorrect
questions.option_d: Statement I is correct but statement II is incorrect

questions.question: A full wave rectifier circuit with diodes $\left(D_1\right)$ and $\left(D_2\right)$ is shown in the figure. If input supply voltage $\mathrm{V}_{\text {in }}=220 \sin (100 \pi t)$ volt, then at $t=15 \mathrm{msec}$
questions.option_a: $\quad D_1$ and $D_2$ both are forward biased
questions.option_b: $\quad D_1$ and $D_2$ both are reverse biased
questions.option_c: $\quad D_1$ is forward biased, $D_2$ is reverse biased
questions.option_d: $\quad D_1$ is reverse biased, $D_2$ is forward biased.

questions.question:
An aircraft landing on a runway at $20 \text{ m/s}$ requires a distance of $500 \text{ m}$ to come to a complete stop after the reverse thrusters are engaged. If the pilot engages the thrusters at a distance of only $250 \text{ m}$ before the end of the runway, the aircraft will reach the end with a speed of $\sqrt{x} \text{ m/s}$. The value of $x$ is ____________.
(Assume constant retardation is produced by the thrusters)

A swimmer can swim with a velocity of $12 \text{ km/h}$ in still water. The water in a river flows with a velocity of $6 \text{ km/h}$. To reach the point on the opposite bank directly across from the starting point, the swimmer must swim at an angle of ____________$^{\circ}$ with respect to the direction of the river flow.

Water is flowing through a horizontal pipe. When the valve is closed, a pressure gauge attached to the pipe reads $P_{initial}$. On opening the valve, the water flows with a velocity of $\sqrt{30} \text{ m/s}$ and the gauge reading drops to $2.0 \times 10^4 \text{ N/m}^2$. The value of $P_{initial}$ is __________ $\text{ N/m}^2$.

(Take density of water $\rho = 10^3 \text{ kg/m}^3$)

The magnetic potential due to a short magnetic dipole at a point on its axial line, located at a distance of $30 \text{ cm}$ from its center, is $2.0 \times 10^{-5} \text{ T m}$. The magnetic moment of the dipole is __________ $A \text{ m}^2$.

(Given: $\frac{\mu_0}{4\pi} = 10^{-7} \text{ T m A}^{-1}$)

In a Young's double slit experiment, the intensities at two points, for the path difference $\frac{\lambda}{6}$ and $\lambda$ ($\lambda$ being the wavelength of light used) are $I_1$ and $I_2$ respectively. If $I_0$ denotes the intensity produced by each one of the individual slits, then the value of $\frac{I_1+I_2}{I_0}$ is _________.

In an atomic spectroscopy experiment, the shortest wavelength observed in the Lyman series of a hydrogen atom is denoted as $x$. Determine the decimal value for the longest wavelength in the Paschen series of the helium ion ($\text{He}^+$) in terms of $x$. (Round to two decimal places)

Two elements, $X$ and $Y$, are members of the carbon family (Group 14) and possess first ionization enthalpy ($\Delta H_{i1}$) values of $708 \text{ kJ mol}^{-1}$ and $715 \text{ kJ mol}^{-1}$, respectively. These values are the lowest among their group members. Determine the chemical nature of the ions $X^{2+}$ and $Y^{4+}$.
questions.option_a: $X^{2+}$ is a reducing agent; $Y^{4+}$ is an oxidizing agent
questions.option_b: $X^{2+}$ is an oxidizing agent; $Y^{4+}$ is a reducing agent
questions.option_c: Both ions act as reducing agents
questions.option_d: Both ions act as oxidizing agents

questions.question: Identify the set of chemical species where the central atoms exhibit $sp^2$, $sp^2$, and $sp$ hybridization respectively:

For a sample of solid copper, the molar heat capacity at constant pressure is given by the expression:

$$C_p(\text{J K}^{-1} \text{ mol}^{-1}) = 23 + 0.01 T$$

where $T$ is the absolute temperature. If the temperature of $3 \text{ moles}$ of copper is raised from $27^{\circ}\text{C}$ to $727^{\circ}\text{C}$ at $1 \text{ atm}$ pressure, calculate the most accurate value of $\Delta H$ in $\text{kJ}$. (Take $0^{\circ}\text{C} = 273 \text{ K}$)

When gaseous hydracids ($HX$) are hydrated, they form species represented as $HX \cdot y\text{H}_2\text{O}$, where $y$ represents the number of water molecules. 

Consider a scenario where the enthalpy of hydration for the formation of a decahydrated hydracid from gaseous $HX$ is $-69.01 \text{ kJ mol}^{-1}$. In another instance, the formation of a higher hydrated species containing $40$ molecules of water of crystallization results in an enthalpy change of $-72.79 \text{ kJ mol}^{-1}$. 

Based on this information, determine the enthalpy of dilution when the decahydrated species is converted into the species with $40$ molecules of water.

For the equilibrium A ⇌ B , the variation of the
rate of the forward (a) and reverse (b) reaction
with time is given by :

The plot of $\mathrm{pH}$-metric titration of weak base $\mathrm{NH}_{4} \mathrm{OH}$ vs strong acid HCl looks like :

$$\text{I. } \text{SO}_4^{2-} \quad \text{II. } \text{MnO}_4^{-} \quad \text{III. } \text{N}^{3-} \quad \text{IV. } \text{BrO}_3^{-}$$

Choose the correct option:

Given below are two statements regarding the Group 15 elements:$$\pmb{\text{Statement I:}} \text{ Analogous to nitrogen forming ammonia, arsenic possesses the ability to form arsine.}$$$$\pmb{\text{Statement II:}} \text{ Antimony is incapable of forming the oxide antimony pentoxide.}$$In the light of the above statements, choose the most appropriate answer from the options given below:
questions.option_a: Both Statement I and Statement II are correct
questions.option_b: Both Statement I and Statement II are incorrect
questions.option_c: Statement I is correct but Statement II is incorrect
questions.option_d: Statement I is incorrect but Statement II is correct

questions.question: Which of the following physical factors is typically absent and does not influence the relative stability of conformations in acyclic (open-chain) organic compounds?
The correct IUPAC name of the given compound is:

The standard Gibbs free energy change ($\Delta G^{\circ}$) for the spontaneous reaction occurring in a certain galvanic cell at $298 \text{ K}$ is $-61.75 \text{ kJ mol}^{-1}$.

$$\text{Zn}(\text{s}) + \text{Fe}^{2+}(\text{aq}) \rightarrow \text{Zn}^{2+}(\text{aq}) + \text{Fe}(\text{s})$$

Based on this energy change, determine the standard cell potential ($E^{\circ}_{\text{cell}}$) for the system in volts.

$\textbf{Given:}$ $1 \text{ F} = 96487 \text{ C mol}^{-1}$

$\textbf{Cell Notation:}$

$$\text{Zn}(\text{s}) \mid \text{Zn}^{2+}(\text{aq}) \parallel \text{Fe}^{2+}(\text{aq}) \mid \text{Fe}(\text{s})$$

For the reaction $$\text{NH}_3(g) + \text{HCl}(g) \rightarrow \text{NH}_4\text{Cl}(s)$$, the initial concentrations of the reactants are related as $[\text{NH}_3]_0 = 8[\text{HCl}]_0$. The half-lives for the disappearance of $\text{NH}_3$ and $\text{HCl}$ are $10\text{ min}$ and $40\text{ min}$, respectively. If both reactants follow first-order kinetics and start reacting at the same time, after how much time will the concentration of both reactants be the same?

Consider the following reaction sequence involving potassium dichromate:

$$\text{K}_2\text{Cr}_2\text{O}_7 \xrightarrow[-\text{H}_2\text{O}]{\text{KOH}} [\text{A}] \xrightarrow[-\text{H}_2\text{O}]{\text{H}_2\text{SO}_4} [\text{B}] + \text{K}_2\text{SO}_4$$

What is the oxidation state of chromium in product $[\text{A}]$ and the number of $\pi$ bonds present in one molecule of product $[\text{B}]$?
Which one of the following cyano complexes would exhibit the lowest value of paramagnetic behaviour?
According to IUPAC nomenclature, sodium nitroprusside $\text{Na}_{2}[\text{Fe}(\text{CN})_{5}\text{NO}]$ is named as:
The structure of the compound that gives a tribromo derivative on treatment with bromine water is:
Which of the following statements about primary amines is $\pmb{\text{false}}$?
questions.option_a: Alkyl amines are stronger bases than aryl amines.
questions.option_b: Alkyl amines react with nitrous acid to produce alcohols.
questions.option_c: Aryl amines react with nitrous acid to produce phenols.
questions.option_d: Alkyl amines are stronger bases than ammonia.

Crystals of oxalic acid weighing $4.5\text{ g}$ are mixed in water to make $250\text{ mL}$ of the solution. The molarity of the resulting solution in $\text{M}$ is $x \times 10^{-1}$. The value of $x$ is _______.
The number of $\text{Cl}= \text{O}$ bonds present in a molecule of perchloric acid is ________.

The reaction rate for the following reversible reaction 
$$[\text{PtCl}_4]^{2-} + \text{H}_2\text{O} \rightleftharpoons [\text{Pt}(\text{H}_2\text{O})\text{Cl}_3]^{-} + \text{Cl}^{-}$$ 
was measured as a function of concentrations of different species. It was observed that: 
$$-\frac{d[[\text{PtCl}_4]^{2-}]}{dt} = 4.8 \times 10^{-5}[[\text{PtCl}_4]^{2-}] - 2.4 \times 10^{-3}[[\text{Pt}(\text{H}_2\text{O})\text{Cl}_3]^{-}][\text{Cl}^{-}]$$ 
where square brackets denote molar concentrations. The value of $K_c \times 100$ for this reaction is _______.

The number of compound(s) given below which contain(s) a carboxylic acid ($-\text{COOH}$) group is __________.

(A) Perchloric acid
(B)  Aspirin
(C) Picric acid
(D) Fumaric acid
(E) Carbolic acid
(F) Ascorbic acid
(G) Sulphanillic acid

The number of white coloured salts among the following is:

(a) $\text{SrSO}_4$
(b) $\text{Mg}(\text{NH}_4)\text{PO}_4$
(c) $\text{BaCrO}_4$
(d) $\text{Mn}(\text{OH})_2$
(e) $\text{PbSO}_4$
(f) $\text{PbCrO}_4$
(g) $\text{AgBr}$
(h) $\text{PbI}_2$
(i) $\text{CaC}_2\text{O}_4$
(j) $\text{Fe}(\text{OH})_2(\text{CH}_3\text{COO})$

Let a function $f(x)$ be defined as:

$$f(x) = \log_{\sqrt{5}} \left( 3 + \cos \left( \frac{3\pi}{4} + \theta \right) + \cos \left( \frac{\pi}{4} + \theta \right) + \cos \left( \frac{\pi}{4} - \theta \right) - \cos \left( \frac{3\pi}{4} - \theta \right) \right)$$

If the range of $f(x)$ is given by $[m, M]$, determine the value of the difference $M - m$.
For a given angle $0 \leq \theta \leq \frac{\pi}{4}$, identify which of the following identities involving infinite series is correct.
If $z = \frac{7 + i\sqrt{51}}{7}$, calculate the modulus $|z|$ and the argument $\arg(z)$.
Suppose $p, q,$ and $r$ are distinct positive real numbers such that the sum of their squares is 1. Under these conditions, determine the upper limit for the value of the expression $pq + qr + rp$.

A set of $24$ identical chocolates is to be distributed among $3$ students. If the requirement is that each student must receive at least two chocolates, determine the total number of distinct ways the distribution can be performed.

Find the coefficient of $x^4$ in the expansion of the expression:
$$\left( \frac{1 - x^6}{1 - x} \right)^3$$
If the final answer is written in the form $\binom{n}{r}$, determine the numerical value of $n - r$.

Consider a geometric progression $b_1, b_2, b_3, \ldots$ where the initial term $b_1 = \frac{1}{8}$ and $b_2 \neq b_1$. Suppose every term in this sequence is the arithmetic mean of the subsequent two terms. Determine the value of the expression:

$$b_{19} + b_{20} + b_1$$
If a straight line passing through the point $P(-3, 4)$ is such that its intercepted portion between the coordinate axes is bisected at $P$, then its equation is :

The foci of a hyperbola are identical to the foci of the ellipse $\frac{x^2}{9} + \frac{y^2}{25} = 1$. If the eccentricity of the hyperbola is $\frac{15}{8}$ times the eccentricity of the ellipse, which of the following points $P$ on the hyperbola satisfies the condition that the smaller focal distance $\min(d_1, d_2)$ is equal to $7\sqrt{\frac{2}{5}} - \frac{8}{3}$?

If the limit

$$\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{\cos(2x) + a\cos(4x) - b}{x^4}$$

is finite, then determine the quadratic equation whose roots are $a$ and $b$.

Suppose a polynomial function $y = g(x)$ is defined for all real numbers such that:

$$g(x) = x^3 + x^2 g'(1) + x g''(2) + g'''(3)$$

Determine the specific value of $g(1)$.

Suppose $A$ and $B$ are two events such that $P(A) = \frac{1}{3}$, $P(B) = \frac{1}{5}$, and $P(A \cup B) = \frac{1}{2}$. Determine the value of the following expression:

$$P(A \mid B') + P(B \mid A')$$

where $A'$ and $B'$ denote the complements of events $A$ and $B$ respectively.

Calculate the value of the following summation:

$$\sum_{k=1}^{100} \left( \tan^{-1}\left( 2k^2 \right) \right)^{-1}$$

Suppose $p, q, r \in \mathbf{R}$ are constants such that the following limit exists and equals $3$:

$$\lim_{x \to 0} \frac{x^2 \sin(px) + (r - 1)e^{x^2}}{\sin(2x) - qx} = 3$$

Let $S = \{p, q, r\}$ be a set containing these constants. Determine the minimum sum of any two distinct elements in $S$.

The displacement of a particle moving along a straight line is described by the function $y = f(t) = pt^2 + qt + r$ for $t > 0$, where $p, q, r > 1$. Determine the specific time $t$ within the interval $[2, 3]$ at which the instantaneous velocity of the particle is exactly equal to its average velocity over that same interval.

Let $F_n(x)$ be a function defined for all real numbers such that it satisfies the condition:

$$|F_n(a) - F_n(b)| \le (a - b)^2$$

for all $a, b \in \mathbf{R}$. If $F_n(0) = 1$, determine the value of $F_n(x)$ for any $x \in \mathbf{R}$.

Evaluate the following definite integral:

$$\int_0^1 \frac{1}{1 + x} \, dx$$
The area (in sq. units) of the region $\{(x,y) \in \mathbb{R}^{2} : x^{2} \le y \le 3 - 2x\}$ is :

A differentiable function $y = g(x)$ satisfies the following integral identity for all $x > 0$:

$${x^2}g(x) - x = 4\int\limits_0^x {tg(t)dt} $$

If the curve passes through the point $(1, 2/3)$, determine the specific value of $18 \cdot g(3)$.

Let the values of $p$, for which the shortest distance between the lines
$$L_1: \frac{x+1}{3} = \frac{y}{4} = \frac{z}{5},$$ 
$$L_2: \vec{r} = (p \hat{i} + 2 \hat{j} + \hat{k}) + \lambda(2 \hat{i} + 3 \hat{j} + 4 \hat{k})$$
is $\frac{1}{\sqrt{6}}$, be $a$ and $b$ (where $a < b$). Determine the length of the latus rectum of the ellipse defined by:
$$\frac{x^2}{a^2} + \frac{y^2}{b^2} = 1$$

A prime number is a natural number greater than 1 that has no positive divisors other than 1 and itself.

Let $T = \{q_1, q_2, \ldots, q_{10}\}$ denote the collection of the first ten prime numbers. Define $B = T \cup Q$, where $Q$ represents the set of all possible products formed by multiplying distinct elements from $T$.

Consider the set $R$ of all ordered pairs $(x, y)$ where $x \in T$, $y \in B$, and $x$ divides $y$. Determine the cardinality of $R$, denoted by $|R|$.

Determine the number of integral values of $\alpha$ for which the line $$3x + 4y = \alpha$$ intersects the circle $$x^2 + y^2 - 2x - 4y + 4 = 0$$ at two distinct points. If the range of $\alpha$ is $(a, b)$, report the value of $|b - a|$ __________.

A parabola $y^2 = 12x$ has a chord passing through its focus with length $d$ and slope $m < \sqrt{3}$. If the distance from the origin to this chord is $S$, then determine the value of $4S^2d$ __________.

Consider an ellipse $\mathcal{E}$ defined by $$\frac{x^2}{p^2} + \frac{y^2}{q^2} = 1$$ having eccentricity $\frac{1}{2}$ with foci located at $(\pm 2, 0)$. Let $\mathcal{C}$ denote the circle of smallest area that completely encloses this ellipse. Consider a variable triangle $\Delta PQR$ where vertex $P$ lies on circle $\mathcal{C}$, and side $QR$ of length $2p$ is parallel to the major axis of $\mathcal{E}$ and passes through the point where $\mathcal{E}$ intersects the negative $y$-axis. If the maximum area of triangle $\Delta PQR$ can be expressed as $4(r + \sqrt{s})$, then determine the value of $r + s$ __________.

For real numbers $\mu$, $\nu$, $\rho$, and $\sigma$, if

$$\int \frac{(x^2 - 1) + \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{x^2 + 1}{x}\right)}{(x^4 + 3x^2 + 1)\tan^{-1}\left(\frac{x^2 + 1}{x}\right)} dx$$

$$= \mu \log_e\left(\tan^{-1}\left(\frac{x^2 + 1}{x}\right)\right) + \nu \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{\rho(x^2 - 1)}{x}\right) + \sigma \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{x^2 + 1}{x}\right) + C$$

where $C$ is an arbitrary constant, then determine the value of $10(\mu + \nu\rho + \sigma)$ __________.
